It is with a heavy heart that I’m giving 3 stars because if not for this incident, it would be 5 hands down - the macaroons are the best I’ve ever had and it’s such a cute little place. HOWEVER. On Monday afternoon (11 March) I came in to the shop for the first time. There was one gentlemen and one lady at the behind the counter. I asked the gentlemen if any sweets were vegan and he told me ‘only macaroons’ were. The two then laughed quietly - now I can’t be sure if this was because of the lie they just told me or if the gentlemen was just genuinely mistaken and they laughed about something completely different. Whether it was ignorance or absolute disrespect for the consumer - the shop should train their employees better. Today on Wednesday morning (13 March) I came in to buy the macaroons again and asked the two different and very nice ladies if macaroons were vegan and they said they were not but they were gluten free. Two completely opposite experiences these two times - one with disrespectful or ignorant staff and the other with polite and knowledgeable. Such a disgrace for the shop for the first experience which I’ll repeat is a shame cause I’d be a regular there. And on the side note - I eat vegan because I choose to, but some people may have allergies and intolerances and the shop could run into serious problems for misleading the customer as to the ingredients of their products.

I ordered one of each flavor to hunt and hope for a hidden gem, but I can happily save my time and tastebuds for something better.
